premise_source_doc_sentence: Another strategy which is different from conventional vaccine is to induce the T cell arm of the immune response using viral vectors , adenoviral vectors that contain large parts of the hepatitis C virus genome itself , to induce a T cell immune response against hepatitis C.

In particular , the charity aims to increase awareness and testing ; to provide services on a national and local level to people with , affected by , or at risk of contracting hepatitis C ; and to campaign for greater public understanding of the impact of hepatitis C .
Hepatitis C is an infectious disease caused by the hepatitis C virus  (  HCV  )  that primarily affects the liver .
A hepatitis C vaccine , a vaccine capable of protecting against hepatitis C , is not available .
The Hepatitis C Trust is a registered charity in England and Scotland that campaigns on various issues related to hepatitis C .
